2026-05-13: Bugfix text body not displayed on terminals with light background

v1.33 beta12 Tuseday 11 November 2025 PL
Two important bug fixes :

* The UTF-8 conversion did not work right when the first character of a
  line was ÅÄÖ or åäö. Very strange bug that took a while to figure out.
  Now fixed = UTF-8 conversion should now be fully completed :D.
* List conferences with ansi off is now truly with ansi off.
* Conferences with files now displays the suffix (F).
 
v1.33 beta11 Wednesday 15 October 2025 PL
* I think we're running out of bugs for the moment, so here are some new
  features (let's hope they don't introduce too many new bugs) :

  * Completely re-designed "List conferences"-command with colors and 
    cleaner output. We now show the number of unread posts of each 
    conference, and for now I skipped the "S" and "F" columns because a 
    normal user probably don't know what they stood for anyways? 
    We need a new discrete way to indicate that the conference has files 
    though.
  * New command "Fotnot / Footnote" let's you add a footnote to your own 
    posts in local conferences, for corrections and such, this is much 
    cleaner than having to add comments on your own posts.
  * New commands "Hylla / Praise" let's caller like a post. Command status
    <user> shows all liked posts by the user, status <conference> shows 
    a list of all liked posts. Also added the commands "Avhylla / 
    Unpraise". This took some effort as I had to figure out the structure 
    of Sklaffkom's database and some AI-help was needed (again) for the 
    deep technical stuff. Got plans for some kind of "Karma"-system and 
    these two new commands will be a big part of that.
   * New command "Ändra mötesbeskrivning" lets you add, change or remove 
    the description of a conference.

v1.33 beta10 Saturday 27 September 2025 PL
* Small tweaks in debuglog function for safety and cleaner output
* New macro dlog for easier injection of logging all over the place ;).
* Making posts and follow-ups now have very extensive logging in place.
* Also most file operations (upload / download / list files / describe)
  are extensively logged now.
* lib/raw.io disabled logging for now as it created log files on every
  (I think) newstoss run. We probably don't need this and if we do we
  can enable it again.
* It turned out "fputs("\004", pipe);" (^D) for news posts was redudant, 
  it seems, so it's commented out for now. We'll keep an eye on it.
* cmd_describe partly rewritten to avoid memory corruption. This took a 
  while to figure out, but should be super safe now across all POSIX-
  systems.
* Humanized, nicely aligned file sizes in cmd_list_files.
* Tweaks to cmd_unlink (delete <file>) - verbose logging and more robust 
  error checking with appropriate output.

V1.33 beta9a Saturday 27 September 2025 PL
* This is the version we're shipping to github, after a day or so trying
  figure out why inews did not work on FreeBSD anymore :D. Should be fixed
  now, and I can move on to beta10 :).

v1.33 beta 9 Thursday 25 September 2025 PL
Yet another session at the hospital :
* new function display_logout displays etc/logout during logout.
  logout.swe and logout.eng for multilingual systems.
  display_news moved to helpers.c to keep original codebase tidy.
* new function clear_screen - more robust handling of clear_screen
  available outside of commands.c.
* safer logging in admin.c - prevents segfault when user permissions
  are wrong
* The command "Börja om" has probably never worked since there was no
  logic for handling restarts in sklaffkom.c at all. Now there is, and
  "Börja om" should work as intended.
* improved display_langfile, should now always display correct language
* CRUCIAL FIX : Proper logout sequence displaying hayes commands like
  in the good old days. Also in sklaffact now, first impression last.
* New command "Clear" same as "Cls" to avoid confusion amongst us
  Linux-freaks.
* Small tweaks to the file_exists function, mostly to keep compiler
  happier in 2025.
* lib/sys_error.c rewritten due to causing havoc while modifying other
  functions (forgot which ones)
* Makefile improvement : mailtoss and newstoss copied to SKLAFFBIN
  instead of hardcoded /usr/local/bin (my bad)
* More "junk" (my own code) moved to lib/helpers.c to keep the original
  codebase as original as possible. This work will continue.
* Serious sklaffrc bug fixed where numlines was written to the wrong file
  (still worked though, just missing a /).
* display_header moved to helpers.c after a heroic ctrl-v adventure 
  with lost curly braces. Found and restored. All curly braces are well.
* The hayes modem emulation is now displayed during logout only, not
  during restart (which would defeat the purpose)

